title: American Horror Story: Double Feature Recap & Review - CAPE FEAR & PALE
author: EJ Moreno
comment: YO!! This was the most solid two episodes of AHS in such a long ass time. I’m here for it
Loved it. I wouldn't change a thing about it. Love so many characters are back. Can't wait to see what happens next.
As an artist/writer/performer myself (who has dabbled in naughtiness for inspiration... this particular season has hit me in the sweet spot. I would totally take the lil black pill
Sarah Paulson character is more scary looking than the creatures. It took me the second episode to even realize that was her.
"We're here for the mountain bike and the locked ipad." 😂😂😂 best line
description:
American Horror Story Season 10 Part 1 is here, and it’s back with so much insanity. Let’s dive into AHS: Double Feature Episode 1 and Episode 2, where we meet our new characters and the weirdest Sarah Paulson role yet.

American Horror Story: Double Feature is the tenth season, created by Ryan Murphy and Brad Falchuk. The season will be divided into two parts: Red Tide and Death Valley

Returning cast members from previous seasons include Frances Conroy, Leslie Grossman, Billie Lourd, Sarah Paulson, Evan Peters, Adina Porter, Lily Rabe, Angelica Ross, Finn Wittrock, Denis O'Hare, and Cody Fern along with new cast members Macaulay Culkin and Neal McDonough.
